- Honestly, I don't know.

5
00:00:09,044 --> 00:00:11,011
Carlos and Gaby made a deal.

6
00:00:11,053 --> 00:00:13,347
I did remarry my ex,
but it was only because

7
00:00:13,388 --> 00:00:15,766
- he has great health insurance.
- Susan made amends.

8
00:00:15,807 --> 00:00:17,768
You know, I never thought
I'd have such a good time

9
00:00:17,810 --> 00:00:19,921
hanging out with my girlfriend
and her husband.

10
00:00:19,962 --> 00:00:22,305
- And Mike...
- Didn't she mention we dated?

11
00:00:22,340 --> 00:00:24,926
- ... made a confession...
- Liar! You've just been leading me on!

12
00:00:24,967 --> 00:00:27,428
You're obviously still in love
with this guy!

13
00:00:27,470 --> 00:00:28,971
- ... of his own.

14
00:00:29,013 --> 00:00:30,973
On her first day of sobriety,

15
00:00:31,015 --> 00:00:33,059
Bree Van De Kamp found an old cork,

16
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:38,230
which reminded her just how
much she craved Chablis.

17
00:00:38,272 --> 00:00:42,297
So she called her sponsor,
who came over with a DVD

18
00:00:42,332 --> 00:00:46,287
which they watched
till her craving had passed.

19
00:00:46,322 --> 00:00:50,076
Five days later, after she
developed a thirst for Merlot,

20
00:00:50,117 --> 00:00:52,752
Peter arrived with a deck of cards.

21
00:00:52,787 --> 00:00:55,289
The next week, he brought
over Chinese takeout

22
00:00:55,324 --> 00:00:57,256
because Bree had told him

23
00:00:57,291 --> 00:01:01,671
she was consumed by thoughts
of vintage Chardonnay.

24
00:01:01,712 --> 00:01:07,383
By her 20th day of sobriety, Bree had
stopped thinking about alcohol altogether

25
00:01:07,426 --> 00:01:12,306
because her thoughts were
now centered elsewhere.

26
00:01:12,348 --> 00:01:14,225
Hmm...

27
00:01:16,894 --> 00:01:20,606
I'm curious, Peter. What is the
easiest way to overcome addiction?

28
00:01:20,648 --> 00:01:23,401
Oh, some folks try shock therapy.

29
00:01:23,442 --> 00:01:25,403
Other use, uh, hypnosis.

30
00:01:25,444 --> 00:01:27,405
But taking it one day at a time

31
00:01:27,446 --> 00:01:29,407
still makes the most sense to me.

32
00:01:29,448 --> 00:01:30,408
Why?

33
00:01:30,449 --> 00:01:34,787
I don't know. I guess I'm just
impatient to get on with my life.

34
00:01:38,374 --> 00:01:39,834
What are you doing?

35
00:01:39,875 --> 00:01:42,795
I was just giving you a little kiss.

36
00:01:42,837 --> 00:01:44,463
Why?

37
00:01:44,505 --> 00:01:46,966
Well, it's just my way of saying thank you

38
00:01:47,008 --> 00:01:49,761
for everything you've done for
me over the past few weeks.

39
00:01:50,803 --> 00:01:53,354
What's... wrong?

40
00:01:53,389 --> 00:01:56,392
This is gonna seem like it's
coming out of left field,

41
00:01:56,427 --> 00:01:58,894
but in addition to being
a recovering alcoholic,

42
00:01:58,929 --> 00:02:01,147
