my two favorite ladies.

114
00:05:40,858 --> 00:05:43,486
Try the cheese.
That's the best part.

115
00:05:43,528 --> 00:05:46,405
You mean, two of your three favorite ladies.

116
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:49,158
You know, when you add in Edie.

117
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,042
Right! Of course.

118
00:05:51,077 --> 00:05:54,330
And speaking of Edie, I have some big news.

119
00:05:54,372 --> 00:05:57,124
I finally did it. I popped the question.

120
00:05:57,166 --> 00:05:59,001
Oh! Congratulations, Dad!

121
00:05:59,043 --> 00:06:00,753
Yeah... congratulations.

122
00:06:00,795 --> 00:06:04,048
Um, what happened to waiting six months?

123
00:06:04,090 --> 00:06:06,641
Edie and I aren't
getting married tomorrow.

124
00:06:06,676 --> 00:06:10,555
It takes months to plan
a classy wedding, you know?

125
00:06:10,596 --> 00:06:13,891
Remember ours, hmm? You had
to have it outdoors, huh?

126
00:06:13,933 --> 00:06:16,310
Ugh. It poured.

127
00:06:16,352 --> 00:06:18,020
I could have murdered that weatherman.

128
00:06:18,062 --> 00:06:21,315
We were all crammed under
this little gazebo thing.

129
00:06:21,357 --> 00:06:23,317
It was hysterical.

130
00:06:23,359 --> 00:06:25,736
I thought the whole wedding day was ruined.

131
00:06:25,771 --> 00:06:27,738
I loved it! It felt spontaneous.

132
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:32,410
All our friends gathered
close around us, hmm?

133
00:06:32,451 --> 00:06:35,002
Remember?

134
00:06:35,037 --> 00:06:38,666
You said it was the happiest
day of your life.

135
00:06:42,962 --> 00:06:44,922
Just like you marrying Edie

136
00:06:44,964 --> 00:06:47,383
will be the happiest day of her life.

137
00:06:47,425 --> 00:06:49,510
Yeah. Right.

138
00:06:49,552 --> 00:06:51,679
Her, too.

139
00:06:51,714 --> 00:06:53,806
Toodles.

140
00:06:58,477 --> 00:06:59,916
Oh, hi.

141
00:06:59,951 --> 00:07:01,355
Hello.

142
00:07:01,397 --> 00:07:04,525
Andrew said it was all right
for me to get a cream soda.

143
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:06,861
Uh, sure. Help yourself.

144
00:07:06,903 --> 00:07:09,071
There's also frosted glasses in the freezer.

145
00:07:09,106 --> 00:07:11,240
Can is fine, but thank you.

146
00:07:11,282 --> 00:07:13,910
Oh, and, uh, I left a list for you

147
00:07:13,951 --> 00:07:16,787
of the witnesses we'll be deposing.

148
00:07:16,829 --> 00:07:18,956
It's, uh, there on the counter.

149
00:07:29,342 --> 00:07:31,010
Hi.

150
00:07:31,052 --> 00:07:32,220
Hey.

151
00:07:34,555 --> 00:07:37,558
I know that you're still
angry with me, and, um...

152
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:43,105
I wanted to tell you that I have, um...

153
00:07:43,147 --> 00:07:45,942
joined a recovery program.

154
00:07:45,983 --> 00:07:48,201
A.A.

155
00:07:48,236 --> 00:07:51,322
I just wanted you to know that...

156
00:07:51,364 --> 00:07:53,991
and to tell you I'm sorry.

157
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:55,993
You are...

158
00:07:56,035 --> 00:07:58,454
a real friend, and I value your honesty.

159
00:08:00,831 --> 00:08:03,084
Oh, I don't wanna be mad anymore.

160
00:08:03,125 --> 00:08:05,086
And I'm so happy to hear all that,

161
00:08:05,127 --> 00:08:07,755
- and I am so proud of you.
- Oh, thanks,

162
00:08:07,797 --> 00:08:09,757
but I'm not really out of the woods yet.

163
00:08:09,799 --> 00:08:12,635
I still have this whole court
case hanging over my head.

164
00:08:12,670 --> 00:08:14,101
I heard about that.

165
00:08:14,136 --> 00:08:16,430
Andrew's asking to be emancipated?

166
00:08:16,472 --> 00:08:18,432
Yes, and his lawyer is taking
depositions now

167
00:08:18,474 --> 00:08:20,810
to see if I am a fit parent.

168
00:08:20,852 --> 00:08:22,353
Oh.

169
00:08:22,395 --> 00:08:24,856
And considering that mishap
that I had with your kids,

170
00:08:24,897 --> 00:08:27,483
I, uh, I imagine he'll
be anxious to talk to you.

171
00:08:27,825 --> 00:08:29,827
Well, it makes sense, I guess.

172
00:08:29,869 --> 00:08:31,203
Yeah.

173
00:08:31,245 --> 00:08:33,747
Do you have any idea what you might say?

174
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,002
I, um...

175
00:08:41,505 --> 00:08:44,800
I'll focus on your good qualities.

176
00:08:47,303 --> 00:08:49,722
I could not ask for anything more.

177
00:08:49,763 --> 00:08:51,390
Thanks.

178
00:08:51,432 --> 00:08:54,101
- See you around, I hope.
- All right.

179
00:08:54,443 --> 00:08:58,155
That's... not why you
came to apologize, is it?

180
00:08:58,197 --> 00:08:59,656
What do you mean?

181
00:08:59,698 --> 00:09:02,951
To soften me up for the deposition?

182
00:09:02,993 --> 00:09:05,370
Of course not.

183
00:09:08,916 --> 00:09:11,502
Um...

184
00:09:11,543 --> 00:09:15,088
I just want you to understand something.

185
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:17,758
Andrew is making accusations...

186
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:20,552
