511
00:25:49,416 --> 00:25:52,336
had gotten all screwed up,
of course I would've agreed.

512
00:25:52,377 --> 00:25:54,505
Look, Edie, in retrospect...

513
00:25:54,546 --> 00:25:56,715
yes, we didn't think.

514
00:25:56,757 --> 00:26:00,969
We didn't handle this the way
mature adults should have.

515
00:26:01,011 --> 00:26:03,972
He's right. We behaved like children...

516
00:26:04,014 --> 00:26:06,642
naughty, stupid children.

517
00:26:06,683 --> 00:26:10,771
Well, that makes me feel better
that you could admit that.

518
00:26:11,980 --> 00:26:16,068
Because... when naughty children misbehave,

519
00:26:16,110 --> 00:26:18,654
they know that they're gonna
get punished, don't they?

520
00:26:21,782 --> 00:26:22,741
Punished?

521
00:26:22,783 --> 00:26:24,500
At this point,

522
00:26:24,535 --> 00:26:28,122
I'd like to point out that,
uh, it was Karl who proposed.

523
00:26:28,163 --> 00:26:29,838
Karl.

524
00:26:29,873 --> 00:26:33,585
You are gonna throw me an elaborate wedding.

525
00:26:33,627 --> 00:26:36,380
Yes, of course.

526
00:26:36,421 --> 00:26:39,258
Anything, baby.

527
00:26:39,299 --> 00:26:41,767
How elaborate?

528
00:26:41,802 --> 00:26:45,389
Well, figure out exactly what
it is that you could afford,

529
00:26:45,430 --> 00:26:46,932
and triple it.

530
00:26:48,517 --> 00:26:52,146
- As for you...
- Okay, now remember, I'm broke.

531
00:26:52,187 --> 00:26:54,481
I'm well aware of your church mouse status.

532
00:26:54,523 --> 00:26:58,360
I don't intend to lift a finger

533
00:26:58,402 --> 00:27:00,529
during the planning and execution

534
00:27:00,571 --> 00:27:04,575
of this crushingly expensive wedding.

535
00:27:04,616 --> 00:27:06,577
No. No, of course not.

536
00:27:06,618 --> 00:27:09,163
And anything I can do to help...

537
00:27:09,204 --> 00:27:11,707
uh, you know, I would...
I could help with the engagement party.

538
00:27:11,742 --> 00:27:12,833
How's that?

539
00:27:12,875 --> 00:27:16,587
Well, I wasn't planning on inviting you.

540
00:27:16,628 --> 00:27:18,297
But...

541
00:27:18,338 --> 00:27:20,007
I will need a bartender.

542
00:27:22,050 --> 00:27:23,552
Oh, oh, and, um...

543
00:27:23,594 --> 00:27:26,096
make sure you come in through the back door.

544
00:27:34,938 --> 00:27:37,483
You're just in time.

545
00:27:37,524 --> 00:27:42,821
Mrs. Scavo has been sworn in,
so we're all ready to start.

546
00:27:42,863 --> 00:27:43,822
Hey.

547
00:27:43,864 --> 00:27:45,908
Hi.

548
00:27:52,748 --> 00:27:55,042
All right, we are now on the record.

549
00:27:55,077 --> 00:27:57,336
Okay.

550
00:27:57,377 --> 00:28:00,464
Isn't it true that while your
children were in Bree's care,

551
00:28:00,506 --> 00:28:01,965
that she passed out drunk

552
00:28:02,007 --> 00:28:06,136
and allowed them to wander off
to a downtown business district?

553
00:28:10,432 --> 00:28:14,978
My kids don't wander. They scurry, like rats.

554
00:28:15,020 --> 00:28:18,315
- Excuse me?
- Do you know a rat can fit through a hole

555
00:28:18,357 --> 00:28:19,817
the size of a quarter?

556
00:28:19,858 --> 00:28:22,820
Anyway, my children have
that trick down, too.

557
00:28:22,861 --> 00:28:24,404
Mrs. Scavo, are you saying

558
00:28:24,446 --> 00:28:26,573
that you don't hold Mrs.
Van De Kamp responsible

559
00:28:26,608 --> 00:28:28,575
for endangering your children?

560
00:28:28,617 --> 00:28:30,911
No, I don't hold her responsible.

561
00:28:30,953 --> 00:28:34,373
Bree Van De Kamp and I have
known each other a long time.

562
00:28:34,408 --> 00:28:35,839
I trust her completely.

563
00:28:35,874 --> 00:28:38,001
She's a wonderful friend
and a fantastic mother.

564
00:28:38,043 --> 00:28:41,004
She puts the rest of us to shame.

565
00:28:41,046 --> 00:28:44,049
She's lying! Are you gonna let
her get away with this crap?

566
00:28:44,091 --> 00:28:46,093
Please.

567
00:28:47,594 --> 00:28:50,722
Do you consider Mrs. Van De
Kamp to have a drinking problem?

568
00:28:50,764 --> 00:28:53,725
No.

569
00:28:53,767 --> 00:28:56,228
Then why did you line empty wine bottles

570
00:28:56,270 --> 00:28:57,938
up on her front stoop?

571
00:28:57,980 --> 00:29:01,567
I was helping Bree with her recycling.

572
00:29:01,608 --> 00:29:03,819
Do I need to remind you

573
00:29:03,861 --> 00:29:06,447
of the potential consequences of perjury?

574
00:29:06,488 --> 00:29:10,659
No, you don't. In fact, I hate liars.

575
00:29:30,554 --> 00:29:31,513
Hello?

576
00:29:31,555 --> 00:29:34,683
Peter. Hi, it's Bree.

577
00:29:34,725 --> 00:29:36,310
Hey, Bree.

578
00:29:36,351 --> 00:29:39,021
You know, um, if you feel like
you're gonna need a drink,

579
00:29:39,062 --> 00:29:40,689
you should call Donna.

580
00:29:40,731 --> 00:29:43,692
No! No, I-I don't feel like I'm gonna drink.

581
00:29:43,734 --> 00:29:45,778
And if I did, I certainly would call Donna.

582
00:29:45,819 --> 00:29:49,281
I mean, she and I are just...
we're just really clicking.

583
00:29:49,323 --> 00:29:51,450
Oh, that's good. So why are you calling?

584
00:29:51,492 --> 00:29:54,369
I know it's really late notice,
but a friend of mine, uh,

585
00:29:54,411 --> 00:29:56,336
got engaged and she's throwing a party,

586
00:29:56,371 --> 00:29:58,373
and I thought, um, maybe you'd like to come.

587
00:29:58,408 --> 00:30:01,585
- Bree...
- Well, you're not my sponsor anymore,

588
00:30:01,627 --> 00:30:03,962
so I assume this is allowable.

589
00:30:04,004 --> 00:30:06,138
I mean, it's just a casual get-together.

590
00:30:06,173 --> 00:30:09,092
And they're having sushi.
You do like sushi, don't you?

591
00:30:09,134 --> 00:30:10,093
Bree...

592
00:30:15,474 --> 00:30:19,144
Okay, Peter, I just really...

593
00:30:19,179 --> 00:30:21,021
need us to be friends.

594
00:30:21,063 --> 00:30:23,023
When I'm with you, I'm not myself,

595
00:30:23,065 --> 00:30:24,274
which is a good thing.

596
00:30:24,316 --> 00:30:27,152
I can... I can relax when I'm with you

597
00:30:27,194 --> 00:30:30,656
in a way that I can't
when I'm with other people.

598
00:30:31,949 --> 00:30:34,952
With them, I have to pretend
that I have it all together,

599
00:30:34,993 --> 00:30:37,371
but...

600
00:30:37,412 --> 00:30:40,541
you know that I don't, so
it's just so much easier.

601
00:30:40,576 --> 00:30:42,793
Come on, it's just a...

602
00:30:42,835 --> 00:30:44,795
it's just a dumb old party.

603
00:30:44,837 --> 00:30:46,880
Bree...

604
00:30:46,922 --> 00:30:48,590
do not call me again.

605
00:30:54,721 --> 00:30:56,682
Oh!

606
00:30:56,723 --> 00:30:58,808
Paul! I am so glad you made it.

607
00:30:58,843 --> 00:31:00,894
I appreciate the invitation, Edie.

608
00:31:00,936 --> 00:31:03,063
Although, frankly, I'm a
little surprised to get it

609
00:31:03,105 --> 00:31:05,441
considering how people in this
neighborhood feel about me.

610
00:31:05,482 --> 00:31:09,403
Oh. You know me. I like to be inclusive.

611
00:31:09,445 --> 00:31:10,904
Ooh! It's heavy.

612
00:31:13,031 --> 00:31:15,325
Uh, unh-unh. This is flat.

613
00:31:15,360 --> 00:31:17,619
I think I'd like, um...

614
00:31:17,661 --> 00:31:19,121
a Rusty Nail.

615
00:31:19,163 --> 00:31:20,789
A what now?

616
00:31:20,831 --> 00:31:21,999
It's a cocktail,

617
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:23,709
well, I'm not really sure what's in it.

618
00:31:23,750 --> 00:31:27,463
But it sounds obscure and
complicated, so chop-chop.

619
00:31:28,672 --> 00:31:30,549
Be right there.

620
00:31:30,591 --> 00:31:32,641
Hey, hey. Put that down. We gotta go.

621
00:31:32,676 --> 00:31:35,436
- Our birth mother just went into labor.
- What?

622
00:31:35,471 --> 00:31:39,016
- That's fantastic!
- Yeah, can you believe it?
We're gonna be parents.

623
00:31:39,057 --> 00:31:41,059
I'll go get the car. Come on.

624
00:31:41,101 --> 00:31:43,020
We were supposed to have four weeks.

625
00:31:43,061 --> 00:31:46,064
She promised to me the baby wasn't
due for four more weeks.

626
00:31:46,106 --> 00:31:48,525
We don't have anything! We don't...
we don't have diapers,

627
00:31:48,567 --> 00:31:50,861
and we don't have the stuff babies drink.

628
00:31:50,903 --> 00:31:53,154
- Formula.
- Exactly. We're not ready.

629
00:31:54,072 --> 00:31:56,408
You know, this is a total inconvenience.

630
00:31:56,450 --> 00:32:00,078
Welcome to parenthood. Come on.

631
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:02,080
This is your father's bartender bible.

632
00:32:02,122 --> 00:32:05,125
- See if you can find a
recipe for a Rusty Nail.
- Okay.

633
00:32:10,422 --> 00:32:11,507
Um, Mom?

634
00:32:14,301 --> 00:32:16,553
Where'd you find that?

635
00:32:16,595 --> 00:32:20,808
It was stuck in here between
a Pink Squirrel and a Pisco Sour.

636
00:32:20,849 --> 00:32:23,227
Oh.

637
00:32:23,268 --> 00:32:26,730
Well, why is your father keeping this?

638
00:32:26,772 --> 00:32:29,233
Why do you think?

639
00:32:37,282 --> 00:32:38,909
Hey, Susie.

640
00:32:38,951 --> 00:32:40,410
Karl, this marriage...

641
00:32:40,452 --> 00:32:41,912
our marriage, this fake marriage,

642
00:32:41,954 --> 00:32:44,164
that's what it is, right? Fake.

643
00:32:44,206 --> 00:32:45,707
What are you talking about?

644
00:32:45,749 --> 00:32:48,043
What's this?

645
00:32:48,085 --> 00:32:49,628
Nothing.

646
00:32:49,670 --> 00:32:52,005
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

647
00:32:52,047 --> 00:32:56,677
Okay, then, repeat after me.

648
00:32:56,718 --> 00:32:58,178
"Our marriage is fake,

649
00:32:58,220 --> 00:33:00,848
"and I'm going to marry
the woman I really love...

650
00:33:00,889 --> 00:33:02,224
Edie Britt."

651
00:33:02,266 --> 00:33:04,351
If that's what you want me to say.

652
00:33:04,393 --> 00:33:07,229
No, no, no, no! It's not about
what I want you to say.

653
00:33:07,271 --> 00:33:12,693
You have to want to say
that you want to marry Edie.

654
00:33:12,734 --> 00:33:14,840
Don't worry about this, Susie.

655
00:33:14,875 --> 00:33:16,947
Why are you hanging on to that?

656
00:33:16,989 --> 00:33:19,283
I need to look at it from time to time.

657
00:33:19,324 --> 00:33:20,492
Why?

658
00:33:24,830 --> 00:33:27,541
Consider it my punishment.

659
00:33:27,583 --> 00:33:31,253
For screwing up the best thing
that ever happened to me.

660
00:33:33,338 --> 00:33:38,218
Oh. Oh, no, no, no.
This is not happening.

661
00:33:38,260 --> 00:33:40,936
No, wha... mmm. Mmm!

662
00:33:40,971 --> 00:33:43,515
Oh, Karl! Oh! Will you...

663
00:33:43,557 --> 00:33:46,143
- Are you crazy?!
- Just tell me what to do, Susie.

664
00:33:46,178 --> 00:33:48,103
If you want me to marry Edie, I will.

665
00:33:48,145 --> 00:33:50,939
You want me to call off
the wedding, I'll do it.

666
00:33:50,981 --> 00:33:53,400
I'll do whatever you want.
I'm putty.

667
00:33:53,442 --> 00:33:55,277
Karl! Whoa!

668
00:33:57,905 --> 00:33:59,371
What are you doing?

669
00:33:59,406 --> 00:34:02,951
I'm, just, uh, putting away some coats.

670
00:34:02,993 --> 00:34:04,328
Oh.

671
00:34:04,369 --> 00:34:06,538
Well, it's time to open my presents.

672
00:34:06,580 --> 00:34:07,581
Let's go.

673
00:34:24,973 --> 00:34:26,475
Oh, hello.

674
00:34:26,510 --> 00:34:27,726
Hi.

675
00:34:27,768 --> 00:34:30,104
Hi. Um, I need some advice
from a professional.

676
00:34:30,139 --> 00:34:32,071
I'd like to get stinking drunk.

677
00:34:32,106 --> 00:34:35,818
Do you have anything that can
accomplish that in a hurry?

678
00:34:39,947 --> 00:34:41,907
I forgot the Lamaze book in my purse!

679
00:34:41,949 --> 00:34:44,451
Oh, forget it. Come on.
Let's go. We'll wing it.

680
00:34:47,788 --> 00:34:49,832
Oh, we missed it!

681
00:34:49,873 --> 00:34:52,251
The kid just slipped right out.

682
00:34:52,292 --> 00:34:53,877
Are you family?

683
00:34:58,882 --> 00:35:00,384
They're the parents.

684
00:35:07,808 --> 00:35:10,769
Would you like to help?

685
00:35:10,804 --> 00:35:12,229
No, thanks.

686
00:35:12,271 --> 00:35:15,941
You guys look like you got it covered.

687
00:35:15,976 --> 00:35:18,110
Oh, are you sure, honey?

688
00:35:18,152 --> 00:35:19,736
Come on, Gaby.

689
00:35:19,778 --> 00:35:21,905
I just, um...

690
00:35:21,947 --> 00:35:23,907
I-I don't wanna do anything to screw it up.

691
00:35:23,949 --> 00:35:26,118
She won't break.

692
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:28,454
Here.

693
00:35:28,495 --> 00:35:29,621
Okay.

694
00:35:33,333 --> 00:35:37,171
Hi.

695
00:35:40,340 --> 00:35:45,012
Oh, honey, you were right.

696
00:35:45,053 --> 00:35:46,597
About what?

697
00:35:50,851 --> 00:35:52,853
It was all worth it.

698
00:36:02,905 --> 00:36:05,824
Serving bowls.
Just what I needed, Lynette.

699
00:36:05,866 --> 00:36:08,786
There's a gift receipt taped
to the bottom of the box.

700
00:36:08,827 --> 00:36:10,579
Oh. Thank God!

701
00:36:12,623 --> 00:36:15,626
Okay, the next one is from Felicia.

702
00:36:15,667 --> 00:36:18,086
I do hope you like it.

703
00:36:18,128 --> 00:36:20,088
Oh, you know what they say...

704
00:36:20,130 --> 00:36:23,801
good things come in small packages.

705
00:36:28,013 --> 00:36:30,224
What is it?

706
00:36:32,643 --> 00:36:33,790
Teeth?

707
00:36:33,825 --> 00:36:34,937
Dentures.

708
00:36:36,897 --> 00:36:39,775
They were my dear sister Martha's.

709
00:36:39,817 --> 00:36:42,778
I'm sure none of you knew,
but she had orthodontic issues

710
00:36:42,820 --> 00:36:45,864
from the time she was a child.

711
00:36:45,906 --> 00:36:49,201
Oh.

712
00:36:49,243 --> 00:36:50,536
Thank you.

713
00:36:50,577 --> 00:36:54,206
I know it's an unconventional
gift for an engagement party,

714
00:36:54,241 --> 00:36:56,416
but you and Martha were
such close friends, Edie.

715
00:36:56,458 --> 00:36:58,418
I wanted you to have something truly personal

716
00:36:58,460 --> 00:36:59,920
to remember her by,

717
00:36:59,962 --> 00:37:03,340
since she left us so... abruptly.

718
00:37:03,375 --> 00:37:04,807
You know,

719
00:37:04,842 --> 00:37:07,136
when Paul Young strangled
her, crushed her windpipe

720
00:37:07,177 --> 00:37:11,890
and buried her alive next to
a garbage-strewn hiking trail.

721
00:37:11,925 --> 00:37:14,560
Felicia, uh... I think you've had enough.

722
00:37:16,270 --> 00:37:19,231
I do apologize if I've offended anyone,

723
00:37:19,273 --> 00:37:22,693
but... while you all are chitchatting

724
00:37:22,734 --> 00:37:24,987
and eating these gummy hors d'oeuvres,

725
00:37:25,028 --> 00:37:26,537
just remember...

726
00:37:26,572 --> 00:37:29,032
you're in the company of a murderer.

727
00:38:04,234 --> 00:38:07,613
Bree? Bree.

728
00:38:13,243 --> 00:38:15,329
Why didn't you call Donna?

729
00:38:15,370 --> 00:38:18,582
Hmm.

730
00:38:18,624 --> 00:38:21,418
I don't need Donna.

731
00:38:21,460 --> 00:38:23,629
I need you.

732
00:38:40,354 --> 00:38:43,357
You know, I don't even like redheads.

733
00:38:47,152 --> 00:38:48,612
Okay, it's my turn.

734
00:38:48,654 --> 00:38:51,205
Shh. In a minute.

735
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:54,493
Come on, you're hogging her.

736
00:38:54,535 --> 00:38:57,412
Tell me! You tell
me who it is, Libby.

737
00:38:57,454 --> 00:38:58,914
Are you drunk?

738
00:38:58,956 --> 00:39:00,874
Who is he, Libby? Hmm?

739
00:39:00,916 --> 00:39:03,001
I got to know.

740
00:39:03,043 --> 00:39:05,546
I already told you, he's just some rodeo guy.

741
00:39:05,587 --> 00:39:07,923
- I don't even remember his name.
- Liar!

742
00:39:09,216 --> 00:39:11,844
What are you doing?

743
00:39:11,885 --> 00:39:13,595
I am gonna light myself on fire.

744
00:39:13,637 --> 00:39:16,807
He's gonna light himself
on fire with coffee liqueur?

745
00:39:16,849 --> 00:39:18,684
Would not have been my choice.

746
00:39:18,725 --> 00:39:21,186
Tell me his name, or I'm gonna do it!

747
00:39:21,228 --> 00:39:22,938
Frank, you're being an idiot.

748
00:39:24,481 --> 00:39:26,191
It was Dale, okay? It was Dale.

749
00:39:26,233 --> 00:39:28,944
Security to maternity.

750
00:39:28,986 --> 00:39:33,038
My brother Dale? He's a kid!

751
00:39:33,073 --> 00:39:35,868
Well, he's 19, Frank.
He knows which end is up.

752
00:39:35,903 --> 00:39:39,538
Wait, what is she saying?

753
00:39:39,573 --> 00:39:41,957
There's a father.

754
00:39:41,999 --> 00:39:43,167
Hey! Hey!

755
00:39:45,335 --> 00:39:46,962
- No.
- Leave me alone!

756
00:39:47,004 --> 00:39:48,630
I'm not giving up the baby.

757
00:39:48,672 --> 00:39:51,341
Let's get him out of here.

758
00:39:51,376 --> 00:39:53,093
No! No!

759
00:39:53,135 --> 00:39:54,970
Security to O.B. Security to O.B., stat.

760
00:39:55,005 --> 00:39:56,972
What the hell are you doing?

761
00:39:57,007 --> 00:39:58,439
Taking our baby home.

762
00:39:58,474 --> 00:40:00,434
She's not ours. The papers
aren't valid anymore.

763
00:40:00,476 --> 00:40:02,269
She has a father.

764
00:40:02,311 --> 00:40:04,271
Do you really wanna leave
this beautiful little girl

765
00:40:04,313 --> 00:40:06,273
with that white trash freak show?!

766
00:40:06,308 --> 00:40:07,941
Huh?

767
00:40:07,983 --> 00:40:09,735
Well, come on, then.

768
00:40:16,700 --> 00:40:18,160
Where?

769
00:40:18,202 --> 00:40:19,828
Maternity. Maternity.

